< Review>
The new store on McHenry is big and located across the street (practically) from another big thrift store. The new store is clean well organized and the staff, very friendly.  The sale items that I purchased were priced right. I especially appreciated the help Maria and others provided. It was so nice to see Alma working at the new store. She is an asset to the Salvation Army and the reason I sat down to writing this review.
Thanks Alma, Maria and others at the Salvation Army</Review>

I was in a car accident in 2009 that left me with a laceration to the scalp, for which I needed medical attention  The resulting scar was about 2 inches across and about half an inch wide.  For 8 years I either had to comb my hair a certain way to hide the scar or had to wear a hat.  I visited Dr. Sean Behnam after reading positive reviews online about people who received hair transplants for balding and wondering if he could do something about my noticeable scar.  Dr. Sean told me that he could treat the scar with a FUE hair transplant procedure that would make the scar invisible.  I communicated to him my fear that the individual transplanted hairs would die in the scar tissue, but he reassured me that they would successfully graft and grow in the scar tissue because of the placental lining solution he uses in the FUE procedure.  I was told to take it easy for about three weeks after surgery, and I did do the follow-up care as Dr. Sean instructed.  The hair started growing out of the scar about three months later and the hair strands eventually become thicker, which surprised me.  The scar is gone.  I can now comb my hair normally and don't have to wear a hat when I cut my hair short.  Dr. Sean transformed my life.  I'm no longer conscientious about the scar like I use to be!  I highly recommend seeing Dr. Sean to treat scalp scars!</Text>

<Text>Just had an FUE procedure done with Dr. Sean. It‚Äôs only been a week, so my review is based on the experience.
I live in the Bay Area but chose Dr. Sean after taking into account multiple factors: 1) member of IAHRS 2) Great reviews on Yelp and Google 3) Amazing Youtube video explaining in great details everything you need to know pre-op, op and post-op. 4) consultation was great. He went over everything: cost, what to expect, what not to expect and other details. 5) Amazing personality. Warm, friendly and professional. You can tell he absolutely loves what he‚Äôs doing and takes great pride in his work
I saw 3 others doctors in NorCal&SoCal + Bosley + virtual consultation from Turkey and finally selected Dr. Sean.
He personally called me the night of procedure, which was very kind of him
On the day of procedure, he evaluated whether FUT or FUE is better for me. We agreed to do FUE. He initially told me he will only do my front and probably no crown this time.
He had a hookah-style laughing gas to get me ready for the numbing. I have very low pain tolerance but I was okay with it. I laid on my stomach for 2 hours while Dr extracted the grafts. I had 1 bathroom break. I would recommend not drinking coffee the morning of operation. The less bathroom breaks you take and the less you move, the more grafts he can extract (don‚Äôt make him lose his momentum). He had 4 nurses who were taking the grafts from doctor and separating them into 1,2 and 3 hair follicles. He told me he was happy to actually extract ~2900 grafts for me!! Which was amazing news. Of course prior to operation I gave him the thumbs up that he can extract as much as possible.
We took a lunch break where I ate and watched his staff work on my grafts. After lunch, they started the insertion. Again, the hookah nitrogen gas and numbing. He made the incisions himself on the front and my crown which I was super happy about.  Once that part was done, two of his staff started inserting the grafts while he monitored them. The staff took turns so not to get tired. Remember, 2900 grafts means: 2900 drilling + 2900 extraction + 2900 incisions + 2900 planting!! So it‚Äôs A LOT of work. The doctor did the ~9000 first three parts himself and the staff did the last part. His staff were amazing!! We watched a movie and were talking about all sorts of things! It was fun.
The second part is tedious. You‚Äôre sitting for a good 4 hours or more. Your legs get super tired but thanks to the hookah laughing gas, you get through it somehow.
Overall, the procedure took almost 11 hours (including morning consultation and prep + lunch and operation and post operation). It‚Äôs a long day. I‚Äôm glad I‚Äôm stayed at the hotel next door to his office so I just walked back to hotel in like 30 seconds.
I saw the doctor next day and also on the day on my flight. He cleaned up my area, cleaned my hat for the airport and went over everything again.

I‚Äôve been back for 2 days now. I send him pictures every morning for him to see and so far so good.

Overall, I was super happy with the experience. Amazing doctor, amazing staff. Let‚Äôs hope for amazing results soon (let‚Äôs hope for somewhere in between Elvis and George Constanta)

Will definitely update this review with results.

Thanks again Dr. Sean and your amazing staff.< /Text><user>105064017659293842251< /user></record>

- FUE Procedure Day -

I arrived early in the morning and they started right away.  Dr. Sean only does one procedure per day, so 100% of the staff attention was on me, and I felt so comfortable the entire time.  The staff was very professional and they were so nice throughout the entire procedure.

There was almost no pain at all!  Dr. Sean has a special technique, that he developed himself, to numb his patients.  It not only makes it easier, but there are no needles!!!  Throughout the entire procedure Dr. Sean explained what was going on and was always available if I had any additional questions.

About half-way through the procedure Dr. Sean's staff brought me a delicious lunch, and they also provided great snacks throughout the day.  They really went above and beyond to make me comfortable!

Before I knew it, I was done!  It went quicker than I thought and I was ready to go back to my hotel room and relax.  They gave me a great post operation kit that had all of the supplies needed to properly clean and protect the procedure.

- Post Procedure -

I went back to his office the next day for a followup appointment and Dr. Sean looked over his work and answered all of my questions.  After that I flew back to Hawaii.  Dr. Sean called me often to make sure things were still looking good, and if I had any questions I could text him directly!  He always would take the time to answer my questions.  It has been 10 Months since my procedure and he still checks in with me to see how I am doing!

- Results -

It has now been 10 Months since the procedure and I could not be happier!  The results are amazing,  and no one has ever asked if I have had hair transplants.  Dr Sean is very talented in the placement of the follicles, he makes the hairline look completely natural. I am in the water almost everyday and I never have to worry about my hairline. (Before the procedure I would put a hat on the second I would get out of the water so people wouldn‚Äôt see my hairline).  I have so much more confidence in myself and it was sooooooo worth it!  He totally has a special skill!  The density is better than I expected and I feel and look great!

Dr. Sean truly cares about his patients and I feel part of the family.  I would totally recommend Dr. Sean to family and friends.<//review>< pictures>

<Text>Back in 2012 my doctor recommended Dr. Behnam when I asked about a hair restoration specialist. That alone says a lot because anyone my doctor recommends is usually excellent in both medical skills and people skills. I still shopped around for a bit but had the hair graft procedure done shortly after with Dr. Behnam. Very quickly I knew I would write them a glowing review, but also knew from doing research beforehand (shopping around) that most of the reviews were from people who'd recently gotten the procedure done, so I thought I'd wait a bit.
So finally after 2 years I decided it's about time I write this review, because after all this time I'm still just as impressed with my experience there. They are extremely people-friendly, it feels more like visiting family than going to a clinic (his twin brother's dermatologist practice is in the same office so it does have a family practice feel.) He's the only doctor I've ever known that actually gives his cell phone number after surgery, so if you have any issues / questions you can contact him immediately. That's amazing- I don't think any other doctor does that.
Even though my doctor recommended Dr. Behnam I still shopped around and quickly found that Dr.  Behnam's practice had the best rates around- I figured probably in part because they have a nice office on the second floor instead of a 7th floor penthouse like some practices, but it's also obvious that Dr. Behnam is not in it for the money- and ultimately that's what makes the biggest difference here. Contrary to so many places, he only does one procedure per day. So you get his full attention and all his effort and energy on doing the best possible job for you instead of rushing through you to get to the next guy on the list. Every other place I looked into did at least 2 patients per day. (one morning, one afternoon)
As for the procedure itself, I was very satisfied with the results and the operation itself. They made me feel comfortable the day of, and after just a few months waiting for the grafts to grow, for the first time in years I could comb my hair backwards instead of hiding my bald spot.
Included in the price are visits for the laser chair thing, which helps stimulate hair growth. So after all those visits I really came to see that these guys are the real deal. Just good people passionate about what they do, no bullshit, and doing a really good job. If you are not a good candidate for the procedure, he will tell you. That kind of honesty is hard to find in an industry that is known for greedily exploiting people's insecurities.
So yeah, in conclusion I highly recommend Dr. Behnam!</Text>< pictures>

< Review>
We were recommended this lender by our broker. In our case it was buying a house, so the lender knew it will be a jumbo loan and we would need to move fast in processing because real estate market is crazy competitive. Lender and Broker sounded confident and assured us that there won't be any problems, we have everything to be approved and get the house within the price range we had.
We sent documents that they asked us to right away, they gave us a pre-approval letter and we started to look for our dream house.
But when we found one and entered escrow, it started to be weirdly slow. We called broker to follow up with our lender everyday to get the status updates, and kept hearing that everything is on-time, moving as it should. Again, we had a jumbo loan, with 20% down, everybody in lender's team knew about it.
Every week we would hear at least twice a week that something would be finished by end of day, it would not be finished, then we were told by tomorrow, and it was about 50% chance that it was done by then.
By this time we were already behind on our schedule. Seller started to get nervous and we had to send him a nice personal letter asking for extension.
We were suppose to be closed on August 14 2021, we packed all of our stuff in boxes, broke down furniture, had renters coming to our condo on 16th, BUT a couple of days prior to our scheduled move date, Lender comes up with a second appraisal requirement and a couple of more documents. That was so unexpected, never mentioned to us that this could be the case. From that point things were moving even slower. Our seller was beyond angry and ready to walk away with our deposit.  We had a call with him and our agents where he yelled at my husband and requested us to pay per diem - 500$ a day and releasing half of our deposit to him due to these issues coming from going with this broker.
We were in so much stress, meanwhile just hearing from broker that we would close tomorrow, but it kept going for 2 more weeks.
Honestly it felt like Lender just wanted to buy time, was not professional or did not have experience with jumbo loans, which they should've told us before we started the process. Lender's incompetence cost us a lot of extra money and stress that we could have avoided going with different broker/lender.</Review>

< user_id>
101535326944917466886< /user_id>
<name>ian betts<//name><Date>1602379733121</Date>< rating>
4<//rating>
< Text>
The park is well built and has a nice variety of obstacles for intermediate and advanced skaters. Do not come here to learn, as there isn't much for very new skaters (try Goleta park). The reason for 4 stars over 5 is the community here makes skating here less fun, especially on weekends. The park is often crowded (because its awesome) and it may take five tries to hit a rail because people are usually in the way. Also, unlike every other park I've ever been to, skaters here get very upset when you wax a ledge or rail. Maybe just the norms of this park, but if you wax a sticky rail, prepare to have an old man with no teeth try to fight you over it (literally no joke). Overall, if you come early or during a weekday, this park is loads of fun, but I would avoid it on weekends and peak hours.<//Text>

< Text>
Clean. Safe. Not filled with bullies.

I love this park! I love the city for giving the kids a legitimate and safe place to skate. There should be more of these parks.  We often question or criticize the generation born after our own. And that's okay because it is what our previous generations have taught us to do. But this is also key to the problems or issues we vocalize about young people. We expect. We expect. We expect. While we give so little. Sure, we give birth (speaking for myself) but we forget that we are not just parents, we should be mentors, listeners and leaders. If every block has a dive bar for me to relax in, then why should we invest less into the future? A simple skate park on every block makes more sense than a liquor store. I know I sound like an unrealistic dreaming hippie but I'm glad I do.  It's the small things that make the most positive changes.<//Text>

<rating>4</rating>< Review>
Order the Walnut Prawns, they're HUGE!

The fried rice was just Ok, the amount was a little small for the order but it tasted good. We also tried the chinese chicken salad, which cane with a delicious tangy sauce on the side that had a tiny bit of heat but was also very sweet. It wasn't a very complicated salad, only 3 ingredients besides the sauce but it was good.

I'll definitely be back and will try their noodles. The menu is straight forward and has a lot of options.< /Review>

< Time>
1554108190912</Time>
<Rate>1</Rate>< Review>
My first visit.... I was very unimpressed.
We were a group of eight.
Our appetizers arrived along with our lunch plates after the sweet and sour soup was served.
I didn't much like the soup, and I noticed most of the others didn't finish their's either.
I ordered the orange chicken with fried rice.
The chicken was mediocre at best, and the fried rice was really white rice with just enough soy sauce to make the rice sorta brown, and mystery meat.
No peas, carrots diced ham, or scrambled egg.
I did excuse myself to use the ladies room,
and the restroom could use a really good cleaning.
The service was attentive for the most part, but we were also the only patrons.
I won't return</Review>

<UserId.>100113231017160575072< /UserId.><date>1467904260340< /date>< Text>
This burrito joint is inside a liquor store, which is a bit odd. The employees were nice and helpful, but my roasted veggie burrito left a bit too be desired. The flavors were just a bit bland. My husband liked his chicken burrito, but it wasn't the best he's ever had, either. The salsa was odd.. simultaneously too sweet and too spicy at the same time. I wanted to love the salsa so I could use it to flavor the burrito a bit more, but I actually preferred the burrito without the salsa. Might stop here again if we need food and we're passing by, but I wouldn't search it out.<//Text>

<rate>1< /rate><user>116789943246902844422< /user><Pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipM-ypGI8TCWl7ly7PW5BsCuH9aL2aVr4CkUb0k2=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]< /Pictures><Date>1530121407230</Date>< text>
My toilets tank stopped receiving water and I decided to call a couple places to see what it would be to have it looked at. This place was the first one I called.

They said for $89 they could come out and diagnose the problem and give me an estimate on what it would be to fix it. While I was on the phone with them I found a couple other options for $50 to come out and do the same thing, so I told them thanks, I will think about it and give them a call back. The lady on the phone then told me hold on, let me talk to the manager and I can get that $89 service fee waived, and so I just went ahead and decided to use them.

The guy who came out was great, nice professional etc. He took a look at my toilet and was able to tell me the problem was my corroded shut off valve stopping the water flow and he did this by connecting a feeder hose to see if water was still flowing just somehow being blocked by the valve. He was quick to diagnose the problem and clear on what it was.
Then I asked for an estimate for this repair. It was $400 - the $89 dollar service fee credit which goes toward the repair so it brought my grand total to $311. That price was absolutely outrageous. The part was a $12 dollar part from home depot. All you need is a wrench to remove and replace it. For me to shut off my water, and remove/replace this piece took me 10 minutes. There isnt anything special involved or any fancy special tools required to do this. It was as simple as unscrewing something and screwing the new one on (and shutting off the water before doing this) It is not rocket science. I have no experience with plumbing and I did it myself.

Anyway the 1 start review is because of the insane pricing. $400 for coming over and replacing a 10$ piece? The labor doesn't even take 20 minutes.

Anyway, I told the guy I was just going to fix it myself because $400 is a bit much unless you could bring the price down. He was firm on the pricing, and said its set by management at most he could call and ask but he knows they wont change it so I went ahead and ended up paying the $89 service fee and that was that.

What confuses me is he could of just knocked like 100 off the price and it would of still been outrageous but I'd of done it. I don't know anyone who wouldn't be happy to make over $200 just to screw some part on. As long as its not totally obscence pricing I'd go with it, but less then 20 minutes of basic labor and screwing on a part that costs 12$ at home depot that they carry for $400 is their normal pricing? You'd have to be a complete idiot to go with that.</text>

< text>
John Stevenson Plumbing was the second plumber I called. First, I tried our regular plumber, but they wanted to charge me their "after-hours" rate at 3:30 in the afternoon and couldn't get anyone here for at least 2 hours. Forget that! I had an active leak I couldn't stop.

When I called JSP, they not only said they would be charging their daytime prices, but they don't charge by the hour--they charge by the job, by what actually needs to be done. Refreshing! Then they had a plumber here in less than 30 minutes, and he was the Field Supervisor, no less.

He was friendly, knowledgeable, and quick. He gave me an estimate, including a new-client discount of about 10%, and explained what he was going to do. We had a whole new pressure regulator and shutoff valve in about an hour! He cleaned up the space, gave us some helpful recommendations for avoiding future leaks, a quick tutorial on turning off the water at the street (which I couldn't figure out how to do before), how to bleed air out of the water lines, and was on his way.

Highly recommended!</text>

After explaining to my husband later on the phone about this diagnosis, he found this hard to believe since we have had this company come before for yearly service to maintain our furnace and to prevent such thing from happening.
